‘And then it just sort of started turning because these people surfaced like stirring up muddy water.’

Mr Morgan said that Americans would be ‘shooting themselves in the head’ if they get rid of President Obama next year after just one term at the White House.

More than 50 per cent of Americans say President Obama is at fault for the dismal state of their economy, a poll revealed on Thursday.

This was a majority for the first time since he took office and will be another concern to a President with an ever-growing list of problems.

